originalText.text:
Avoid this business- they stole part of our tax return.
My family  has been going to this business for years. The process is always the same, the accountant files taxes and then a few weeks later you get a phone call saying that your check is ready to be picked up. You must pay for their services in order to get the check. Last year was the first time I filed taxes on my own since I just graduated college. Since my mother trusted this person, I decided to file with him too. Everything went smoothly until I got a letter from the IRS specifying how much my refund was. I was shocked to find out that there was a difference between what I received and what they sent. I called them to confirm it.

Finding out I was missing money ignited my curiosity and I checked my entire family’s check against the amount the IRS sent. All of us where missing around $300 each. In total, the losses for the entire family reached around $1,000. I tried in vain to get my money back. Since the owner of this establishment was smart enough to keep everything  casual and didn’t give us receipts, I have no leverage. This review is the best I can do to warn others against this despicable business that steals from a mostly poor community.
